args: Please note that this story contains spoilers\nfor Chapter 16 of the main campaign and for\nChelle's adventurer story.
Mmm, yes. I quite like this dress indeed.\nPlace the order at once.
Very good, Your Highness. I am certain the\ntailor will be honored by your patronage.
And what of the...other item\nI asked you to prepare?
All is proceeding smoothly, Your Highness.\nIt could be ready as early as today.
Very good. Tell everyone in the lab\nI look forward to seeing the fruits\nof their hard labor.
Understood. Now begging your pardon,\nI shall continue the preparations.
All according to plan. My new dress is\nready, development of the secret weapon\nis on schedule...
That is everything I need before\ndeparting for North Grastaea.
There are many considerations when\na lady such as myself goes abroad.
Hm, okay. This list says something\nabout a purrty as well?
Oh yes, the party is one of the final\nrequirements for my upcoming travels.
I fail to see the connection.
Your Highness, the princess of North\nGrastaea's Fadden Kingdom has arrived.
Speak of the devil... Bring her through.\nI would receive her at once.
I am Yelda, eldest princess of the\nKingdom of Fadden. It's a pleasure\nto finally meet you.
The pleasure is all mine. I am Chelle,\nthird princess of the Kingdom of Alberia.
Oh, and this is my pactbound dragon,\nCat Sìth.

You are as beautiful as the stories say,
Princess—and your dragon is most divine
as well. It is truly an honor to be standing
here with you both.
The honor is mine, truly. You have my\nthanks for accepting my invitation.
Well then, you must be tired from your\njourney. Please make yourself at home\nin the palace until the welcoming gala.
I am very much looking forward to it,\nPrincess Chelle! Your lively parties\nhave long been the talk of the land.
And who was that just meow?
Were you not listening? She is the princess\nfrom the Kingdom of Fadden.
That's the country in the north you've been\nsending your little kittens to, mmm?
Was all of that in purrperation for today?
It was indeed. I've invited Princess Yelda\nto Chanzelia in order to form an alliance.
As we will soon be heading north, I think\nit behooves us to have as many allies\nthere as possible.
Yes, but why Fadden in purrticular?
Though Fadden is a small kingdom,\nI believe we will soon become the\nbest of allies indeed.
Well, you're usually right about that\nkind of thing.

Eee hee hee! Tonight's party is going to
be an even grander affair than normal!
That is the only proper way to mark
a new friendship, after all.
Ah, so THAT'S why you said the purrty\nwas part of your travel plans.
Quick on the uptake as always, Cat Sìth.\nNow then, aren't we missing someone?
I hear pawsteps as we speak.
Captain Leif of the White Sparrows\nreporting, Your Highness.
You kept me waiting, Leif. Is aught amiss?
Nothing of import, Your Highness.\nIt does me good to see you again.
But goodness! Your outfit is so... Er...
Eee hee hee! It's quite unusual for you\nto comment on my appearance, Leif.
Is this dress not lovely? I had it made\nspecially for the journey north.
It suits you perfectly, Your Highness...
I sense a ＂but＂ at the end of that sentence.\nGo on. Out with it already.
Pray forgive my impudence, Highness,\nbut I find it a touch revealing.
Such a short hem ill suits a member\nof the Alberian royal family.
Eee hee hee! Oh, but this is wonderful!\nI never thought to get the mother hen\ntreatment from YOU of all people!
Have you suddenly developed a sense\nof humor, perchance?
Well then, rest easy, my fussy friend;\nI assure you I have a very good reason\nfor this garment.
A normal dress would be too restrictive\nfor the journey that lies ahead, you see.
This dress is designed for function above\nall else. Do you understand now?
Your reasoning is sound, Princess,\nand yet...
And yet you cannot find a respectable\nplace to set your eyes. Is that it?
Pray do not jest about such things.
Oh, you are no fun.\nBut that's what makes you you.
You know me well, Princess.\nNow then, why was I summoned here?
Surely you have retainers aplenty with\nmore fashion sense than I.
Yes, let us cut to the chase: I have an\nimportant duty that can only be entrusted\nto you, Captain.
I am ever your sword, Highness.\nMight I ask the nature of the task?
You will serve as my escort for the party!
